<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7203> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7203" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A senator in 66, who was condemned in that year under the Lex Calpurnia de ambitu of 67, and deprived of his rank of senator (Cic. Sull. 6; cf. 67). Sallust incorrectly terms him a senator when, with the eques C. Cornelius, he plotted to murder Cicero at the morning salutatio (Cat. 28.1; cf. 17.3), but he may rightly be considered one of the duo equites Romani whom Cicero mentions in Cat. 19. See J. Linderski, Historia 12, 1963, 511-512. Cf. Plut. Cic. 16.1 and App. BC 2.3, who give other names, the former, Marcius and Cethegus, and the latter, Lentulus and Cethegus.\n" .
